      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence residuals and floating-point round-off contributions to QoI uncertainty must be quantified and shown to be negligible relative to discretization error.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence was monitored via residual drop to 1e-5 but no formal quantification of solver round-off or iterative error contribution to hemolysis index was performed. Factor flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5; achieved level remains at 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A formal review of simulation setup, boundary condition assignment, and post-processing scripts must be conducted by an independent analyst to detect operator errors.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation setup or post-processing scripts was conducted. Analyst self-review was performed but does not satisfy the independence requirement at MRL 5. Factor flagged as epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form uncertainty arising from turbulence model selection, hemolysis power law, and non-Newtonian viscosity model must be quantified through sensitivity studies or Bayesian model averaging.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty was acknowledged in narrative but no sensitivity study comparing alternative turbulence models (SST k-omega vs. realizable k-epsilon) or alternative hemolysis correlations was performed. Factor flagged as a critical epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must have documented sources, uncertainty characterization, and sensitivity ranking. Monte Carlo UQ must propagate input uncertainty to hemolysis QoI.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ propagated uncertainty in flow rate, rotational speed, and blood viscosity. Sobol sensitivity indices were computed. However, geometric tolerances on impeller blade dimensions and surface roughness were not included in the input uncertainty characterization, limiting achieved level to 3."
    },
